                                                     Sunny praise bowls over Rohit Sharma
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT            Rohit Sharma                           
	London: Young Rohit Sharma, who has been making the most of being promoted to open in Virender Sehwags absence, has been bowled over by the legendary Sunil Gavaskars praise.         
	Last Saturday, Gavaskar had said that Rohits the one batsman in Indias T20 team with whom he would relate to the most.         
	Reacting, Rohit told The Telegraph: Its the biggest compliment Ive received... Im thankful to Mr Gavaskar.         
	Specifically, Gavaskars comment had been: He (Rohit) can bludgeon the bowling and, at the same time, play classically...                                                                                                                       
